
The current version of nescc can be obtained via:

	git://github.com/tinyprod/nesc.git, master branch

To build nesC from the git repository, you need

automake 
autoconf 2.64 or 2.69 or later
    2.67 and 2.68 are known not to work (problem with libiberty)
emacs
gperf

Directions: in this directory
./Bootstrap (once only after checkout)
./configure
make

To install:
make install

To make a distribution that doesn't need the above tools:
make dist
or: make distdir=<your favourite name for the toplevel directory> dist
